    <h1><b>Terms and Conditions of Adopting a Child in South Africa</b></h1>

<p>
    1. <b>Age:</b> The adoptive parent(s) must be at least 18 years older than the child.<br />
    2. <b>Marital Status:</b> Adoptive parents can be married, unmarried, or in a permanent same-sex relationship.<br />
    3. <b>Income:</b> Adoptive parents must have a stable income and be able to provide for the child's needs.<br />
    4. <b>Health:</b> Adoptive parents must be physically and mentally healthy.<br />
    5. <b>Background Check:</b> Adoptive parents must undergo a background check and provide police clearance certificates.<br />
    6. <b>Home Study:</b> A social worker must conduct a home study to assess the adoptive parents' suitability to adopt.<br />
    7. <b>Adoption Order:</b> The adoption must be finalized through a court order.<br />
</p>

